## âœ… What Role Python Can Have in This Project

You can use Python to create a **backend API/server** that:

### Common backend tasks Python could handle

âœ” Serve data to the Next.js frontend (e.g., resume content, user data)
âœ” Save or fetch data from a database (PostgreSQL, SQLite, MongoDB, etc.)
âœ” Provide authentication (login/register)
âœ” Run some Python logic (e.g., resume parsing, ML processing)
âœ” Connect to external systems, files, or Python libraries

So instead of the frontend running alone, it would talk to a Python backend via HTTP requests (e.g., using `fetch()` in Next.js).

