## ðŸ› ï¸ What Backend Framework to Use in Python

The most common Python backend options:

| Framework   | Best for       | Notes                                       |
| ----------- | -------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| **FastAPI** | Modern APIs    | Very fast, easy, similar to Node.js Express |
| **Django**  | Full framework | Full app with auth, ORM, admin panel        |
| **Flask**   | Simple APIs    | Lightweight, very beginnerâ€‘friendly         |

For your goals (learn Python + backend API), **FastAPI is a great choice** â€” itâ€™s modern, simple, fast, and used in many real projects.

